(1, 'Abdullah Al-Rasheed', '1@opiant.in', '9811772666', 'Mawhiba Center, 3rd Floor, Olaya Main Street, P.O. Box 52681, Riyadh, KSA', 'Dubai', 'UAE', '1990-01-01', 'Male', 'Mohammed Al-Ghamdi Law Firm', '', '', 'f3674879f5e18c7989e02235da302cc9', 1, '2017-06-27 12:47:01', 0, 1, 'Abdullah Alrasheed is an Associate at Mohammed Al-Ghamdi Law Firm, the representative office of international law firm Norton Rose Fulbright US LLP in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia.', '', 'Riyadh, KSA', '44444', 'Business Setup^Corporate and Commercial', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'King Saud University\r\n(LL.B) Law, (Excellent with Honor)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Arabic^English', '1498567869.png', '', '', 'KSA, Riyadh', '', 0),
(2, 'Abdultaiyab Bahrainwala', '2@opiant.in', '9811772666', 'Office 3504, Churchill Tower, Al A\\\'amal St., Business Bay, Dubai, UAE', 'Dubai', 'UAE', '1990-01-01', 'Male', 'Khairallah Advocates &amp; Legal Consultants', '', '', 'e10adc3949ba59abbe56e057f20f883e', 1, '2017-06-27 13:11:17', 0, 1, 'Abdultaiyab Bahrainwala advises on all aspects of UAE commercial law, corporate law and property Law. He holds an LL.M Degree in International Business Law from National University of Singapore jointly conducted at Singapore and Shanghai. During the post graduation he has specialized in International Business Law by reading courses on Banking &amp; International Payments, Comparative Corporate Governance, Cross-Border Transactions &amp; Transnational Commercial Law, International Law, Comparative Corporations Law, International Public Monetary Payment &amp; Settlements System Law, Choice of Law for International Commercial Contracts and International &amp; Commercial Trusts Law. During the post graduation he has worked in the Supreme Court of Singapore, Singapore.', '', 'UAE, Dubai', '', 'Real property^Family^Labor and Employment', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Member of Indian Business and Professional Council, Dubai, United Arab Emirates', ':: Legal Counsel – Khairallah Advocates & Legal Consultants \r\nDubai, United Arab Emirates Feb 2014 – Present \r\n\r\nProviding legal consultation on Construction & Real Estate (disputes+ investments), Corporate & Commercial matters, Family law, Employment law, Banking & Finance, Criminal law etc. \r\n\r\nDrafting, reviewing and commenting on various Agreements/Contracts \r\n\r\nResponsible for client handling/updating and attending first consultation meeting with potential clients \r\n\r\nResponsible for dealing with lawyers within and outside firm as well as responsible to negotiate with Third Party for reaching settlement \r\n\r\nProvide complete legal assistance to the Management and carrying out work as requested that includes researching and writing articles \r\n\r\n:: Legal Advisor – National Group Advocates & Legal Consultants \r\nDubai, United Arab Emirates Nov 2013 – Feb 2014 \r\n\r\n:: Legal Associate – The Legal Group Advocates & Legal Consultants \r\nDubai, United Arab Emirates Oct 2012 – Nov 2013 \r\n\r\nDrafting Contracts/ Agreements and writing memorials \r\n\r\nDocumenting case law and dealing with every type of Dispute Resolution claims \r\n\r\nAssisting partners with all administration functions and providing ongoing legal support \r\n\r\nFollowing up with the arbitrators, arbitration centres (DIAC & ADCCAC), other public \r\n& private institutions such as DFSA & DIFC, updating clients on their matter and ensuring that the procedure is carried out in the proper manner\r\n\r\nHandling arbitration matters starting from dealing with clients, providing legal assistance on client’s matter mostly in the Real Estate and Construction Law areas \r\n\r\nCarrying out property transactions and settlements \r\n\r\nDrafting and reviewing of legal opinions, legal notices, sale and purchase agreements \r\n\r\nAttending arbitration hearings and writing minutes of such hearings \r\n\r\nCase law research, finding correct interpretations of the statutes, writing memorials, documenting case law, finding relevant judicial precedents for cases at hand \r\n\r\nPossess knowledge regarding the working procedures of different institutions in UAE \r\nsuch as DIAC, ADCCAC, DLD, DFSA and DIFC\r\n\r\nAssisting the Managing Partner of the firm in any and every other official task \r\n\r\n:: Legal Intern – Citilegal \\r\\nSingapore Sept 2011 – Oct 2011 \r\n\r\nAssisted lawyers in drafting letters, notices and emails to other law firms and clients \r\nAssisted in compiling documents for upcoming case hearings \r\n\r\nAttended Supreme Court of Singapore along with Senior Associate \r\n\r\nCarrying out legal research \r\n:: Legal Intern – The Legal Group Advocates & Legal Consultants \r\nDubai, United Arab Emirates Nov 2009 – Feb 2010 \r\n\r\nSupported and assisted firm partners with miscellaneous tasks within the office and relevant government departments and committees \r\n\r\nUpdating clients regarding their case proceedings by meeting, telephone conversation and emails \r\n\r\nCommunicating with Dubai Courts and Dubai International Arbitration Centre \r\n\r\nDrafting various legal documents including corporate, real estate and construction agreements as well as general legal notices \r\n\r\nAssisted in marketing of the firm', ':: LLM (Masters in International Business Laws) Jun 2011 – May 2012 \r\nNational University of Singapore, Singapore \r\nEast China University of Political Science and Law, Shanghai, China\r\n\r\n:: B.A.LL.B (Bachelor of Arts and Laws) Jun 2006– May 2011 \r\nThe Maharaja Sayajirao University of Baroda, India \r\n\r\n:: General Course in Intellectual Property Rights Oct 2010 \r\nWorld Intellectual Property Rights Organization (WIPO Academy)\r\n\r\n:: Summer Course on International Law May 2010 \r\nIndian Society of International Law, New Delhi, India \r\n\r\n:: Diploma in Cyber Laws July 2009 \r\nAsian School of Cyber Laws, Government Law College, University of Mumbai, India', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Gujarati^Hindi^English', '1498569205.png', '', '', 'UAE, Dubai', '', 0),
(3, 'Ahmed Elnaggar', '3@opiant.in', '9811772666', 'Office 1803, Twin Tower, Al Khour, Deira, Dubai, UAE', 'Dubai', 'UAE', '1990-01-01', 'Male', 'Dar Al Balagh Advocates and Legal Consultancy', '', '', 'e10adc3949ba59abbe56e057f20f883e', 1, '2017-06-27 15:00:56', 0, 1, 'Ahmed Elnaggar is an experienced Legal Consultant and Corporate Structures Specialist, with over 7 years of local experience as Corporate Structure Legal Advisor. His main expertise is in company formation and company formation regulations throughout all the Free Zones in the UAE as well as with the UAE Economic Department Authorities.\r\n\r\nAhmed has extensive practice expertise and expert knowledge of UAE commercial, corporate and labour laws and has been involved in all stages of company formation and management. He is also able to handle continuing services such as assistance with company management and administration, liquidation of companies, real estate matters and ensuring compliance by regulating corporate governance according to federal and Economic Department laws and regulations as well as to the Free Zones requirements.\r\n\r\nAhmed is an energetic professional, very interested in the legal and compliance trends of the region, actively participating at specific conferences and meetings throughout the region. He also writes articles for specialized publications such as the “Offshore Investment” publication.\r\n\r\nSpecialities: Practising in the field of Corporate Structures, Commercial Law, Merger and Acquisition, Company Formation, Offshore Jurisdictions and Trust Agreements, Labor Law and Real Estate laws.\r\n \r\nFluent in Arabic and English.', '', 'Dubai, UAE', '', 'Immigration^Real property^Labor and Employment^Business Setup^Corporate and Commercial', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Ahmed Elnaggar is a member of Arab Advocates Union.', '- 2014-Present: Dar Al Balagh Advocates and Legal Consultancy as Head of Corporate Structures Dept.\r\n- 2014-Present: LKMB & ELNAGGAR Consulting DMCC as Managing Partner.\r\n- 2010-2013: Swiss ILC Management Services as Head of Legal Affairs Dept.\r\n- 2008-2013: Swiss International Legal Consultant as a Legal Consultant. \r\n- 2006-2008: Elnaggar for Legal Consultations as Paralegal & Trainee.\r\n\r\n- Admitted to the Egyptian Bar in Cairo "2007" \r\n\r\n- 2007-2008: Soldier at the Egyptian Army, as the authorized communication specialist, Inventory Monitor, Procurement and Legal Translator. \r\n- 2004-2006: 18-28 Magazine as a Senior Editor. \r\n- 2002-2004: “CIPE” Center for International Private Enterprise as Entrepreneurship program advisor.', 'BA. Law Cairo University in Egypt \r\n\r\nSeveral Diplomas and Courses in the Legal field. Mainly Corporate Structures, Offshore Jurisdictions, Trust and Foundations, International Humanitarian Law, Wills Drafting, General Contracts Drafting, etc...', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Arabic^English', '1498576001.png', '', '', 'Dubai, UAE', '', 0),
(4, 'Ahmed Odeh', '4@opiant.in', '9811772666', 'Office 704, M Hotel Downtown (former Radisson Blu Hotel Business Bay), Financial Centre Road, Dubai, UAE', 'Dubai', 'UAE', '1990-01-01', 'Male', 'Abu Baker Salem Advocates &amp; Legal Consultants (MIO Law Firm)', '', '', 'e10adc3949ba59abbe56e057f20f883e', 1, '2017-06-27 15:10:09', 0, 1, 'Ahmed Odeh is a legal consultant specializing in civil &amp; criminal dispute resolution in the UAE. Areas of practice also include commercial, real estate, arbitration and labour. \r\n\r\nAhmed also boasts extensive experience identifying and resolving legal disputes between organizations. Moreover, he also showcased proven results in managing legal teams in litigation and corporate services, fostering teamwork for projects such as due diligence and client reporting.\r\n\r\nAhmed regularly appears on the radio and writes legal articles answering common legal questions in the UAE.', '', 'UAE, Dubai', '', 'Litigation^Arbitration^Banking and Finance^Real property^Corporate and Commercial', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Nottingham Law School (GDL, LPC, LLB)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Arabic^English', '1498576298.png', '', '', 'UAE, Dubai', '', 0),
(5, 'Al-Sharif Hasan bin Ali', '5@opiant.in', '9811772666', 'P.O.Box 35135, Amman 11180, Jordan, Amman, Jordan', 'Dubai', 'UAE', '1990-01-01', 'Male', 'Arab Legal Consulting Office', '', '', 'e10adc3949ba59abbe56e057f20f883e', 1, '2017-06-27 15:17:21', 0, 1, '', '', 'Jordan, Amman', '', 'Litigation^Labor and Employment^Corporate and Commercial', '', 'www.alcolawfirm.com', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Law degree', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Arabic^English', '1498576738.png', '', '', 'Jordan, Amman', '', 0),
(6, 'Alaa Momtaz', '6@opiant.in', '9811772666', 'Level 5, Emaar Square Building 3, Downtown Dubai, Dubai, UAE', 'Dubai', 'UAE', '1990-01-01', 'Male', 'Hadef &amp; Partners LLC', '', '', 'e10adc3949ba59abbe56e057f20f883e', 1, '2017-06-27 15:25:55', 0, 1, 'I am an Associate at Dubai office of Hadef & Partners LLC. \r\n\r\nI am a law graduate from Ain Shams University - English Section - Cairo - Egypt holding a Bachelor of Law. I am a bilingual (Arabic\\English) lawyer and have a total of 6 years of full-time work experience, 3 years I have been working in a corporate role in a medium-sized law firm in Egypt, 3 years I am working in a well-reputed law Firm in Dubai (litigation role).   \r\n\r\nI have vast exposure in handling claims related to Commercial and Civil disputes, Criminal cases, Property and Real Estate and Labor matters. I also have significant experience in Commercial and Corporate Laws.  \r\n\r\nI believe that the skills I have acquired in the course of my professional and educational experiences will be valuable assets and of great assistance to the clients.', '', 'UAE, Dubai', '', 'Criminal^Litigation^Labor and Employment', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Egyptian Bar Association / Member since 2/12/2009', 'Hadef & Partners LLC\r\nDubai, UAE \r\nNovember 2016 - Present\r\n\r\nMAD Advocates & Legal Consultants \r\nDubai, UAE \r\nSeptember 2015 - October 2016\r\n  \r\nHorizons & Co. Law Firm \r\nDubai, UAE \r\nOctober 2012 –August 2015  \r\n\r\nAM Law Firm \r\nCairo, Egypt \r\nDecember 2009 - October 2012', 'Bachelor of Laws (LLB) 2008/2009 From the Faculty of Law (English Department), Ain Shams University ASU, with a grade of (Good)', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Arabic^English', '1498577253.png', '', '', 'UAE, Dubai', '', 0),
(7, 'Amanda Lewis', '7@opiant.in', '9811772666', 'Office 3901-3902, Single Business Tower, Sheikh Zayed Road, Dubai, UAE', 'Dubai', 'UAE', '1990-01-01', 'Female', 'United Advocates', '', '', 'e10adc3949ba59abbe56e057f20f883e', 1, '2017-06-27 15:37:22', 0, 1, 'Amanda is an Associate in the Corporate and Commercial team in Dubai. She advises on company set up in the UAE and contract drafting such as Distributor Agreements, Franchise Agreements, Settlement Agreements, Escrow Agreements, and Joint Ventures and drafting other corporate contracts for a wide range of multi-national and local UAE clients. She assists with matters pertaining to Real Estate matters and negotiations. She advises on matters pertaining to Employment and Family Laws as well.  \r\n\r\nAmanda is an Indian national born in the UAE and holds a Bachelor of Laws (LL. B.) from M.S. Ramaiah College of Law in Bangalore. She is admitted to practice with the Bar Council in India. Amanda speaks English, Hindi and Konkani.', '', 'UAE, Dubai', '', 'Family^Labor and Employment^Corporate and Commercial', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Bar Council in India', '', 'Bachelor of Laws (LL. B.) from M.S. Ramaiah College of Law in Bangalore, India', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Hindi^English', '1498577941.png', '', '', 'UAE, Dubai', '', 0),
(8, 'Andrew Lyons', '8@opiant.in', '9811772666', 'Suite 504, Shangri La Offices, Sheikh Zayed Road, Dubai, UAE', 'Dubai', 'UAE', '1990-01-01', 'Male', 'Davidson &amp; Co Legal Consultants', '', '', 'e10adc3949ba59abbe56e057f20f883e', 1, '2017-06-27 15:48:15', 0, 1, 'Andrew Lyons, a Senior Associate at Davidson & Co, was admitted as a solicitor under the Law Society of Scotland. Since joining in 2011, Andrew has played an integral role in the firm\'s dispute resolution practice and has been a finalist for the Litigation and Dispute Resolution Team of the Year, Corporate Counsel Middle East Awards in 2012 and 2014, in association with Legal Week.\r\n\r\nAndrew\'s litigation experience has resulted in his high level involvement in many of the leading cases before the Dubai World Tribunal (DWT) which is presided over by former English Court of Appeal Judges Sir Anthony Evans, Sir John Chadwick and Michael Hwang, the Deputy Chief Justice of the DIFC Courts. Andrew has acted as lead lawyer in what the Judges consider was the first successful claim in the courts of Dubai for compensation for financial loss resulting from negligent misstatement under Article 282 of the UAE Civil Code, Andrew currently advises a wide range of construction, real estate and commercial clients in the UAE, Middle East and North Africa region, and conducts high value arbitrations under the auspices of the DIFC LCIA, DIAC and ICC.\r\n\r\nAndrew has also been recognised for his recent role as part of a working group of Dubai-based legal practitioners engaging to review and provide input in the draft rules governing the DIFC\'s Wills and Probate Registry (DIFC WPR). The DIFC WPR has since been established under the jurisdiction of the DIFC Courts and heralded by the Governor of the DIFC as being "a first for the MENA region".', '', 'UAE, Dubai', '', 'Arbitration^Real property^Corporate and Commercial', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'LLB', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'English', '1498578582.png', '', '', 'UAE, Dubai', '', 0),
