(165, 1, '2017-06-04 04:53:56', '2017-06-04 04:53:56', 'Both the wife and husband must present in the Court of Law at the time of filing the Petition for Mutual Consent Divorce. Both parties must wait for six months (mandatory) and if the disputes are not resolved between them and have to file the separate Affidavits praying the Hon’ble Court to dissolve their marriage and the Hon’ble Court will pass a Decree of Divorce under Mutual Consent, dissolving the Marriage and if the disputes are resolved within these 6 months, both the spouses are at liberty to withdraw the Mutual Divorce Petition.', 'Both the wife and husband must present in the Court', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cute-robot-2', '', '', '2017-06-08 11:01:09', '2017-06-08 11:01:09', '', 0, 'http://35.154.128.159:83/?p=165', 0, 'post', '', 0),
